
    =======================================================================
                     ESTERIAN CONQUEST HISTORY OF REVISIONS
    =======================================================================

    Edited:  07/29/1992
    Current EC Version: 1.50: Multi-node galactic battle game that supports
        7 major BBS door file formats and is tested on configurations using
        NOVELL(tm), Lantastic(tm), and Desqview(tm).

    NEW: Two new Fleet missions; an intelligence database that remembers
        and displays planet information that players encounter; features to
        speed up order entry such as auto-commission from all planets,
        ability to order a group of fleets at a time, and enhanced fleet
        reports; Registration Key file that allows sysops to convert
        revised test-drive versions to registered versions on their BBSs;
        and much more...

    We kept on listening to our users and found out what they wanted most.
    The result is a much improved and more playable version of Esterian
    Conquest.  Users will enjoy the new missions, the intelligence
    database, and the new fleet views to help plan their missions.  Sysops
    will appreciate our new key file system.  With your key file, you can
    "unlock" the registered features of any test drive version 1.x so that
    you simply download a new test drive and have it behave as a registered
    version (no more postage & handling fees for any future 1.x versions).

    VERSION 1.50 will be sent to all registered users for a shipping &
    handling fee of $4.00.


    -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    VERSION 1.50 (Released 07/29/92):
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------

    USER INTERFACE (ECGAME):
       1. Two New Missions: (a) RENDEZVOUS - fleets move to and merge at a
             specified sector.  (b) SALVAGE - fleets move to a planet and
             are salvaged as production points at half their value.
       2. GROUP ORDERS: order up to 500 fleets on the same mission at the
             same time.  Save time over ordering them individually.
       3. INTELLIGENCE DATABASE: See the status of any planet you viewed or
             scouted.
       4. AUTO-COMMISSION: Commission Fleets and starbases in all stardocks
             with one command.  Scouts are commissioned into individual
             fleets.
       5. FLEET VIEW ENHANCEMENTS: You can now view fleets in order of
             increasing distance from a specified sector.  When viewing by
             ID or Mission, you can now specify a starting value.
       6. MESSAGE AND RESULT ENHANCEMENTS: View all messages and results
             nonstop.  Delete all messages or all results in one step.
       7. DETACH AND TRANSFER IMPROVEMENTS: Detach or transfer ships from a
             fleet without aborting the original mission.  The original
             mission aborts only if the original fleet cannot continue it.
       8. CHANGE FLEET SPEED as well as ROE and ID.
       9. EMPIRE LISTS now show previous year's Planets owned & production.



                                            WHAT'S NEW FOR EC v1.20   - 2 -

    VERSION 1.50 (Changes Continued):
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------

    MAINTENANCE (ECMAINT)
       1. IMPROVED MEMORY MANAGEMENT - ECMAINT requires less memory.
       2. NEW COMBAT SIMULATIONS - damage from fleet-to-fleet or fleet-to-
             planet combat is more realistic.  Large fleets no longer
             demolish small fleets without taking some damage of their own.
             Similarly, planets are better able to defend themselves from
             invading fleets.
       3. ECMAINT /C option now works to close files and force unclaimed
             empires to become rogues.


    -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    VERSION 1.11 (Released 05/25/91):
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------

    KNOWN BUGS THAT WERE EXTERMINATED:
       1. Fleets occasionally refused to attack planets.
       2. On rare occasions, fleets with orders to join a host fleet
             mistakenly thought their host was destroyed.
       3. Some planets with all armies destroyed suddenly gained a very
             large number of armies.
       4. Starbases were incorrectly listing fleets as escorts even after
             the fleets left them.
       5. Planets were allowed to have blank names.
       6. Snoop could not be turned off.

    NEW FEATURES:
       1. Fleets can now be listed by destination.  Fleets with the same
             destination are sorted by ETA so you can tell the order in
             which they will arrive.
       2. Brief fleet reports now show the fleets' ROE and ETA.
       3. The stardate now appears in the Rankings file.
       4. Sysops can now assign interrupt request (IRQ) numbers and
             hardware flow control to COM1, COM2, COM3, and COM4.

    NEW ECFIX UTILITY:
       We have added the ECFIX utility to restore game files in the
       unlikely event that they become corrupted.  In some cases, messages
       and recent orders may be lost.  However, our tests show that
       restored games are very close to the undamaged ones.



    -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    VERSION 1.10 (Released 03/01/91):
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------

       1. Now supports these BBS Software packages: PCBOARD, GAP, RBBS,
       QBBS, RA, FoReM, WILDCAT, SPITFIRE, WWIV, PHOENIX, and any BBS
       package that can generate one of the following door files:
       PCBOARD.SYS, DOOR.SYS (GAP standard), DORINFOx.DEF, SFDOORS.DAT,
       CALLINFO.BBS, INFO.BBS, or CHAIN.TXT.



                                            WHAT'S NEW FOR EC v1.20   - 3 -

    VERSION 1.10 (Continued)
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------
       2. When running ECGAME, you can specify the door file name or just
          the path and it will hunt for a valid door file.
             Ex:  PCGAME \BBS\DOOR.SYS  (specific file name)
                  PCGAME \BBS           (search for file in BBS directory)

       3. More stable interrupt-handling routines to prevent some rare
          clashes with other interrupt-driven software such as
          Lantastic(tm).

       4. Esterian Conquest is now Desqview(tm) aware.

       5. A new FIRST-TIME menu for users to browse a game before joining.
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------


    -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    VERSION 1.02 (Released 01/07/91):
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------
       1. Corrected minor bug which occasionally would not let users into
          the game at late hours.

       2. Beep alarms for the users no longer echo on the sysop side.

       3. Streamlined and modularized internal programming (the files are
          smaller and run more efficiently).
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------


    -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    VERSION 1.01 (Released 01/02/91):
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------
       1. Corrected PO box address which was wrong in earlier
       documentation.
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------





















